There are three '''sawmills''' in ''[[Old School RuneScape]]''. The [[sawmill operator]] working there can turn four kinds of [[logs]] into [[planks]] for a fee, and also sells [[Construction]] supplies: [[saw]]s, [[bolt of cloth|bolts of cloth]] and three kinds of [[nails]], they share the same stock. Players can have their logs converted to planks by using the sawmill operator's "''Buy planks''" option. He is able to create [[plank]]s, [[oak plank]]s, [[teak plank]]s, and [[mahogany plank]]s for the player assuming they have the requisite '''unnoted''' logs and enough [[coins]].

One sawmill is in the [[Lumber Yard]] north-east of [[Varrock]], another is in the [[Woodcutting Guild]] and the third is in [[Prifddinas]]. The sawmill in the Woodcutting Guild is closer to a bank than the one in the Lumber Yard, although 75% [[Hosidius]] [[favour]] and level 60 in [[woodcutting]] is required in order to enter the Woodcutting Guild. The sawmill in Prifddinas requires completion of [[Song of the Elves]].
[[File:Sawmill interface.png|thumb|The interface to convert logs into planks.]]
